TITLE: Using Input Helpers in Telegraf for File Handling
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the new Input helpers to create InputFile objects from different sources such as local files, buffers, and URLs. This provides a cleaner abstraction for handling file inputs when sending media to Telegram.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telegraf/telegraf/blob/v4/release-notes/4.10.0.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { Telegraf, Input } from "telegraf";
const bot = new Telegraf(token);

bot.telegram.sendVideo(chatId, Input.fromLocalFile("../assets/cats.mp4"));

bot.telegram.sendDocument(chatId, Input.fromBuffer(buf));

bot.command("cat", ctx => {
  ctx.sendPhoto(Input.fromURL("https://funny-cats.example/cats.jpg"))
});
```

